column503: survey_post.1.player.survey_strategy_free_text
I was disappointed that the other players started to keep their coins towards the end of the task, but I wanted to maximise my earnings so I kept mine too.
I chose allshire mostly so the team benefitted but chose me towards the end as everyone else was choosing themselves
I tried to forecast how other players would chose to invest based on the information given for previous rounds.
When people started keeping their coins that is what i did, because less people were selecting Allshire
I was hoping that everyone would work together but greed got the better of us.
My strategy was to mostly play westville because I knew only two of us needed to pick it to get coins.
I tried to make as much money as possible by being selfish but basing my decisions on what the rest of the group was doing.
I wanted everyone to maxamise their coins, therefore read the statistics at the end of each round to see what everyone else was doing
it started off a collective strategy to do better for the team and over the game became more individualistic.
I thought keeping the coin would be good if I want to earn at least 1 point rather than 0

I started thinking i would always pick Allshire but when others were picking just to keep the coin it made me keep the coin sometimes but in the main I wanted everyone to have a good outcome despite some being selfish so I mainly picked Allshire

At first I tried to make sure everyone got some but when I saw other people were being greedy I joined them.  I tried a second time to vote for the good of the group a few times but when I saw people were being greedy I once again joined them.

For the first few goes I always went Allshire to increase the chances of everyone getting the second best option, once I realised that most people were going for Allshire every round I started keeping the coin to maximise my own earnings.

frustrating that you didn't know if it was the same person keeping their coin each time or if people were taking it in turns. felt like there was one who was keeping it every time which made me more likely to try and keep mine sometimes too
The obvious thing to do was go for Allshire so we all got the bonus.

Good game, good insight on investments and how each decisions affects one an other and how your aim in investements can vary. Your decisions can change from round to round judgining on how you done on the previous investments which make you want to cahnge you stratergy slightly to achieve your goal of either making more money or working together to have balance and for everyone to do well.
frustrated that other players began to keep coins for them self
Just went with keeping me coin to maximize my total.
I do not trust other players, especially when money is involved. Because there is no chat option, I had to think about myself and my own strategy, so I opted for a guaranteed coin each round.
no other comments
I tried to maximise profits. I tried to encourage others to invest in Westville.
I started by trying to support Allshire but found not many people were doing that so I found it easier to support Westville
Observed other responses then kept my coin mostly

At first I was just choosing Allshire in order to maximise profits but later in the game when everyone switched to keeping their coin and that was no longer working- I switched to keeping my coin.     Until I saw someone in Westville had put coins into Westville and only 2 players needed to do that to get more profit than keeping your coin. I switched to that after noticing.
Initially I wanted everyone to do well, but once the majrority started clicking "keep coin" I also switched to "keep coin".
I changed strategy halfway through and it made no difference
We only clicked Westville or keep for ourselves
I was annoyed at the two selfish players who was gaining from our coins and keeping their own.

The maximum return was if at least 4 people invested in Allshire.   It was always probable that some individuals would choose to keep the coin as it only needed four people to invest in Allshire for all of us to get the maximum return.  However to maximise returns for everyone it was safest to always invest in Allshire.
Keeping the coin seemed to me to be the best option.
I felt that as long as 4 were voting Allshire I could still make a healthy bonus. If I started to keep the coin I felt the others would too and that would drop my rounds coins from 2.5 to 1
People seemed to want the whole group to benefit
intersting
I did want to try and encourage the Allshire target but had to respond to other player's decisions

To be completely honest I found this game rather boring.      I played generally to maximise allshire profit as this seemed the best way to get biggest bonus. Alternating with occasionally keeping the coin for myself just for variety

I chose to invest in Allshire during round one to see what the other players were also investing in. Once I realised the target would be met without me I took a risk by keeping my coin and intended to continue doing so until people stopped investing in Allshire, then I would adjust my strategy. It worked out well until the last round.
Interesting - how would it have changed if we knew who had voted which way? And, selfishness is only profitable up to a point. Nobody cared about Westville or Eastburg.
Interesting survey and I did feel I could not trust the other players. Ha Ha Ha
I realised that most people were voting for Allshire so if I voted to keep the coin that I would increase my winnings. It took several rounds to predict what the rest of the group may do.
great game! other players were sneaky
It would appear the strategies of ohter players changed during the game

The strategy I went for was to choose what would be best for myself every time! i.e for the most part I chose "Allshire" because it's the most amount of coins you can get for each round. You don't benefit from keeping the coin unless other people do it, so I only chose to keep the coin when it looked like a number of people were doing the same.
Seemed sensible to stick to allshire
found the game very hard .

Given the scenario presented, it's hard to conclude that the "other players" were real unless they were extraordinarily bad at maths. I have to assume the other players were simulated, because it's impossible to believe that people would not work to maximise their earnings when there is no real downside for them.
I tried to predict what others would do, if I thought there would be enough players investing in Allshire I saved my coin to maximise my earnings.
I found the circle thing a bit odd.
Disappointing that some people decided to try and take advantage of everyone else picking AllShire - could have ended up with everyone trying that and then all losing out.
I was pleased to see the group were reliably choosing options to increase all our earnings.
it took a while to load
I would alternate selecting Allshire and myself. When numbers from Allshire started to increase I would select myself to better my chances of getting more
Good game, no issues

I was disheartened during the game at the lack of awareness shown by the other players, and their self-interest. I viewed the interest of the group as the highest priority, especially since doing so assured everyone of the highest guaranteed return each round. However it seemed that others preferred to play for personal gain without thinking of the better return they could achieve by considering others.
It was frustrating to see participants change to try and maximise their own outcome
I wanted to vote for Allshire so the team could get more together but it seems more logical to keep the coin. Even though I did try it a couple of times it seems the best way was to be selfish.
nothing

4 of us consistently voted all and made the bonus, but 2 were consistently parasitic, taking both the bonus and their coin back. Because of this, we were at steady state with the all voters reluctant to try and be greedy in case all was lost. However, we did have a period of all trying to be greedy to, from my perspective, try and force the parasitic members to be fairer, which was unsuccessful so we went back to voting all. I am split between thinking the parasitic voters are good or bad, as they increase the overall prosperity but take all of the additional share.

I was playing extremely selfishly, but trying to select for the better of the group in some situations, in order to encourage the rest of the group to choose allshire on the times where I kept the coin for myself.
I noticed that the majority of the player were choosing Allshire which gave me the opportunity to keep some of my coins and still earn Allshire coins
NONE
I wanted to invest in allshire until I realised i could get away with keeping the coin for a while but this backfired towards the end

I thought it made most sense to always give the coin to Allshire because if everyone did that then we would also receive a good amount of winnings, but if we started to compete against each other then there was more of a chance of receiving lower winnings.
I Just thought of the best way of coming out with something. 1 coin is better than 0 and 3.5 coins are better than 2.5

It was an enjoyable and fun game. I tried to maximise my winnings  by trying to predict when most people would click on Westville. The majority of my choices were with Allshire, as it was a steady earner
I felt that betting on Allshire would likely achieve the most income
I feel like most other players were aiming for the same strategy by trying to meet the Allshire target to best maximise total coins earned.
I thought everyone would choose allshire every time. I tended to look at the previous choices and if there was a pattern follow it, ultimately i wanted to win the most coins.    Good game - well done
As Allshire was continually receiving 4+ votes there was no need for me to alter my strategy. If this had changed consistently then I would have changed strategy to maximise coin collection.
tried to maximise my income and predict how many others would click certain options
if i would see 5 investing in allshire i would keep my coin for the next round

I chose Allshire for each round, because I thought (and hoped) that the other players would realise that using that tactic would maximise everyone's earnings. Fortunately the majority of the group also realised and did the same.
i just picked allshire all the time
Trying to mix keeping the coin and voting Allshire to make sure that the 2.5 was won each time
I was trying to maximise everyone's winnings
no
I wanted to do what seemed fair and ensured the whole group got payment.

Given the explanation of how the game worked it was clear to me that everyone, irrespective of whether they were in Westville or Eastburgh, should invest in Allshire to maximise the return for all.  Why some did not do this suggests they did not understand the rules.
No issues  Decision was made by previous group decision to maximise outcome
there was a majority who chose Allshire so that we all earned coins
just tried to maximise my coins

Investing in allshire offered the best return, so I kept at it. I was tempted to keep my coin when we had a surplus of investers, but I knew if we ever fell under the investment threshold then trust would be shattered and we might never regain that min 4 investment, which would leave us all worse off if we're just keeping out coin. So I thought it was more worthwhile sticking with the allshire investment. I planned to switch to westville investment if allshire wasn't reaching the threshold, but that didn't happen.

I was optimistic that most people wouldn't be selfish and would chose the option that would get everybody 2.5 coins. I would be interested to know if they same person chose to keep their coin each time!
I was good fun and I enjoyed trying to figure out what others might do
I tried to share at first, but then tried to maximise my own earnings

I was a little bit put out by the fact that Westville kept contributing to Allshire, reasonably consistently, but Eastburgh was maximising coins by voting for itself AND getting the Allshire coins as well.
I just selected Allshite each time - I thought being consistent would encourage other people to do the same.

I thought that the best odds for maximising winnings was to always keep it for myself as each round I was guaranteed something as the others were a gamble and I could have received nothing and I could potentially make more but still be guaranteed one coin.
We all wanted to do well

At first I was determined to get the Allshire bonus as it is higher and the whole group will benefit so should help but then other players were selfish/dumb and stopped contributing so I had to change tactics and invest in Westville instead. I then stuck with Westville for the rest of the game as it helps other players and makes more money even if it isn't the most possible. I felt annoyed when people were silly but grateful when people helped the group.

I was hoping that Allshire would meet the target in each round as I feel that would have been a fair outcome.  I cannot understand the reasoning of the people who chose to keep the coin.  I could not keep the coin as that would be selfish.
N/A

I was annoyed at the person who kept their coin as they won that plus the aylshire bonus.So I a couple of times chose to keep my coin so that aylshire wouldnt have enough people and the person keeping their coin would lose out.
I just went for the average 2.5 return with the odd keep the option
It worked well thank you
It was interesting to see people keeping the coin and in some cases meaning no one got points

I didn't think the Westville target could be met so I stuck with Allshire and took whatever bonuses came my way. I'm not greedy, so I wasn't too bothered by what bonuses I got, it just seemed like a logical move.
I kept pocketing my coin and then everyone else was selecting Allshare, I played dirty but got the most coins.
i started off randomly then started to choose the option that would guarantee a payment

The fact that the other players played so consistently for Allshire definitely affected my decision making, as I felt far more confident in trying to maximise my own winnings.    If the other players had played differently, so would I. If it became clear that there was a preference for choosing Westville/Eastburgh over Allshire, it would have been unlikely I would have chosen that and less likely I would have kept the coin for myself.
No one was voting for Westville, so that was pointless for me to vote for
enough though some were greedily keeping the coin, best outcome is still for me to invest to maximise chance of 4 coin investment in Allshire.
Once everyone realised that we could all win by not being to greedy it transpired that keeping the same choice was favourable.

I wanted to maximise my coins by keeping my own coin. But after a while others started to do the same as me. This lowered my gain and I had to pick allshare so that others would start to do the same. Then I went back to keeping my coin to maximise my gain again.
Most seemed to want to invest in Allshire so I also did for 2/3 of the time but I wanted to boost my earnings by keeping the coin the other time.
I felt the strategy was obvious, which was to invest in Allshire each time. It wasn't worth me keeping the coin as that would entice others to do the same and no target would be met.
Thought it was best if we all went for the same
I usually focused on what benefited the whole group most, although at times I would go in favour of my own group when I saw that another group member needed support.
i just played safe most of the times then went greedy some times too
Really enjoyable game and experience!
Once enough players were contributing to Allville, I felt that was the right time to maximise my earnings by keeping the coin.
just followed what was working and continued voting the same way
Seemed nobody else was interested in Allville, so I tended to go for Westville for the +2, occasionally sneaking in a keep in the hope of getting a +3
I tried to look at previous results to see what people were thinking.
when i saw the others were all voting one way i changed my "equal share' strategy to all for allshire then realised i could make more for myslef by keeping the coin/....
Enjoyed the game, surprised about the lack of interest in Allshire

I enjoyed the game and found it to be a good test of my ability to cooperate and make strategic decisions. I was impressed by how quickly the other players were able to learn and adapt their strategies
I was just hoping everyone else was choosing allshire like me to maximise our winnings

The Allshire option benefiting both teams has tactically no benefit. The objective would be to have 2 players voting for their towns, with the 3rd taking the extra coin for maximum points. The first team to do this has the lead, and the game is concluded as long as the choices do not change.
I just felt getting the most winnings was the most important thing.

I didn't need to use a strategy as the other players (mostly) voted with Allshire, resulting in decent earnings for the entire group. I was expecting this might change part-way through the experiment however it remained the same.
The game was lovely just learn to keep the coin when necessary, invest in westville or Allshire.
I just wanted to get the maximum I could.

I decided that the best strategy to ensure a higher chance of very high score was to target my 'village' with my coins. Getting two of three for 2 coins a round was much easier than getting 4 of 6 for 2.5. It was lower risk with similar payout. It worked, my 'team' figured it out very quickly and I think we would have got that payout of 2 70-80% of the time at least.
Annoyed that someonekept trying to do better for themselves

I wanted the group to favour Allshire so played coins for that early on, then when it was clear we were in a trend of most people playing that, I tried to maximise my own returns by keeping a coin, but playing it once others dropped out and started to do the same.

My strategy was to look for patterns on when people would vary between keeping the coin for themselves and giving it to allshire. When only 1 person voted to keep the coin in the previous round, I gambled that I would also be able to keep the coin next round and chances are allshire would still hit 4. If 2 people said they would keep the coin in the previous round (including myself) I would switch to allshire. I got riskier with this strategy the further into the game I went to maximise reward.

I was getting annoyed that people were choosing to keep the coin, but i knew if i was selfish too then the Allshire wouldn't meet the target and we'd all miss out on the 2.5 coins that round. I thought people keeping the coin were being greedy and unfair.

Choosing Allshire was the easiest option and seemed to work well to get coins as the other players were clearly playing the same strategy and the goal was often met.   Was slightly annoyed that some other players were able to keep the coin and therefore get that as well as the bonus from Allshire. I attempted to do this once/twice however both times the Allshire bonus was not met so I got less coins than usual.
like everyone chose the same for max profit
at first i was going to try and help us all win but then i got the feeling everyone was staying east or west so i did the same
The game was good. It was nice to see everyone playing the same game and spreading the coins

I noticed enough people went for all shire that I could maximise my return by opting to pick my own coin as well. If allshire failed to reach 4 i would have switched back to allshire in the hope of getting it to 4.    If 4 had chose allshire and 1 westville, then id have also chosen westville (however this never happened).
I think we all had the same strategy of getting the most winnings for the group
I just wanted to go with the safest option

I played it safe by investing in Allshire in the beginning to get a gist of the other players, and alternated between keeping a coin and Allshire. I also realised that Westville and allshire investments were having the same results, so I began investing in Westville in hopes that someone would join me and so we can maximise our profits together, but no one came.
i felt the best way to maximise the amount of coins was to choose allville and as long as there were 4 of us doing so then we maximise our earnings

i got an ally on my team westville so i just made sure i put my coi on ours and hoped my ally kept doing aswell so we made our target because eastburgh was keeping coin for themselves so the allshire would not meet target.
its a nice game and i enjoyed
We scored higher when everyone invested in Allshire so it made sense for everyone to invest in Allshire.
i wasnt convinced there were real other people

This was fun.  The game has an element of free-riding built into it. I was happy to free-ride.  When two many other 'people' also opted to free-ride, I was happy to not free ride the next round so that the group reached its quorum of 4 to each get the 2.5 coins.
It felt important to ensure the greatest average payout over the study, and that involved consistency choosing allshire
I started off hoping my fellow team mates would vote for our home town but they didn't so I need took the view to look after myself and not support them.
Allshire for every round, theres no need to be greedy just make sure everyone gets something everytime.
i felt like we should have all invested in Allshire to maximize everyone's winnings
I felt sad that some people wanted to try and gain a little extra instead of doing well as a group.
It interesting. I sort of follow very quickly what group most often are clicked and do the same.
I became frustrated that no one was clicking Westville, on numerous occasions I was the only one clicking Westville. I needed only one other person so that we can reach the bonus.
I was disappointed that the players seemed to be playing for themselves and hadn't recognised the advantage of working together

I used the first round to see what everyone else was doing, if we had of all chosen Allshire I would have continued to choose that option. But they didnt so just kept my coins each round to increase my coins.
when I felt more people had started to go Allshire I would switch to keep the coin in the hope I would get 3.5

I found that in the beginning of the game most of the players had decided to go with Allshire and towards the end of the game it came across like they then decided to gain as many coins individually instead of as a team

I wanted everyone to do well to maxmise their coins. Whenit became apparent that everyone else was working to the same theory I kept the same option. However, did contemplate on the last round keeping my coing as it wouldn't affect any other round (as another person did) but chose to stick to the status quo
I really enjoyed the experience but i decided upon a strategy that i thought would give me the most coins!
Once my team were clicking on westville regularly I knew that I could keep my coin.
wanted the best result for everyone

I was pleased with my strategy and felt the other players cooperated well. I think this is the best outcome for everybody. I felt the game went on a bit to long, but appreciate this opportunity to earn some money and to help research. Thank you.

I was glad that everyone stuck to Allshire as this was the best outcome for everybody. I was tempted to keep the coin at around 18 as I knew it was up to 25. But I waited until 20 which turned out to be the last round. So I should have gone earlier!
Obviously I am not sure but I felt most people were choosing the same answer throughout the game as they believed their strategy worked
I strongly believed that always investing into Allshire was the best decision. I was unconcerned with my own benefit, I just wanted everyone to do well.
none
good game i had a fair group, it's best to be the most fair since it benefits you and everyone

i thought if we worked together then we'd all get the highest outcome. part of me was thinking to keep the coin every now and then but then i decided against it because i didnt want to lose the groups trust
One (may not always have been the same) player started 'cheating' (keeping the coin) after about round 5. The rest of kept
The more I clicked on Allshire the more I got the 2.5 bonus. When I went greedy and kept the coin I lost money so Allshire was the best option.
1 person always kept the coin. Frustrating but I did not let it influence my strategy
I focused on everyone so kept my choice the same to maximise the chances of everyone getting something.
It worked out better for the entire team to vote the same
mostly wanted everyone to get the most/same but had a few greedy rounds
thank you
Going for Allshire meant getting the most on average for everybody
Was nice seeing everyone almost always choose best outcome for allshire

I figured that to maximise the coins earnt per person in my local group (Westville), four participants would need to invest in Allshire and two would need to invest in my local group (Westville), however that outcome (2+2.5 = 4.5 coin return) seemed unlikely.  I did consider keeping the coin although contributing to Allshire, resulting in a more consistent return each round for all participants was a more desirable outcome for me.
I thought I could get the most (along with everyone else) if we chose allshire each time. I had faith that other people would think this way as well and for the most part was correct
I kept the coin in the first round to see what everybody else would do and when they all invested into Allshire I just kept investing in myself and I was able to get most of the coins.
It was interesting
Fun and interesting survey
i enjoyed the game
I went for the greatest benefit for the most players. I'm a little disappointed in those who kept the coin for moral reasons but overall, it didn't affect the outcome of the game
very interesting as the game wore on the strategy used by different players
I first supported Westville more but then realised everyone was supporting Allshire so I went along with that to increase my earnings.

I knew one person was always keeping their coin so it was hard to judge when to keep mine and also 'hope' the remaining members of the group would continue to choose Allshire to maximize my outcome. this only worked once. The safest 'bet' was to choose Allshire but that in turn helped those that did keep there coin.

From the instructions, it seemed that the best strategy for everyone would be to invest in Allshire, so that the citizens of both Westville and Eastburgh would benefit. I was pleased to see that enough of the other participants seemed to have the same thoughts, so that the Allshire target was met in the first couple of rounds. It was a bit disappointing that individuals tried to get more coins for themselves and jeopardised funding for the community as a whole but it was pleasing to see that only 1 or 2 individuals continued this strategy in most rounds so that the Allshire target was met anyway most of the time. I really enjoyed the game and thought the survey was very nicely designed. Many thanks.
I invested more to gain more coins and kept some coins to my self when I presumed some would invest to get more coins and it would be an advantage for me
Once I realise that the majority were clicking Allshire I decided to keep my coin a few times
My strategy at first was to maximise earnings for either allshire or westville, but after a while my strategy changed to maximise earnings for myself

I felt investing in Allshire was the best option to give a fair share to everyone without being too greedy.  You could get the best payoff by keeping the coin and hoping enough other people invest but that is greedy and not for the common good.  There was a couple of wobbles where someone from Westville kept the coin for a few rounds but on the whole all Westville took a similar view.  2 from Eastburgh invested in Eastburgh throughout (for some reason).
I felt early on that my Westville team were in agreement that we would continue to focus on our coins being invested there so that's what I focused on from there on
I noticed that I and another continuously voted for our team, with another two voting for their team, too. I felt almost obligated to continue voting for my team so the other person didn't lose out.
I noticed that keeping coin was the most profitable so did that most often
I wanted to get the best outcome for everyone. When players started not choosing Allshire I changed my choice once or twice to protect myself
I was seeing what the other players were doing, ideal I think was keep my coin and others go for Allshire
I wanted to get max points for all players
I was trying to maximize my profit by donating to Allshire when it was low and when it wasn't I would keep my coin to maximize my profit.
my aim was purely to gain as many coins for myself as possible , hoping the other westville members to also make the right choices to maximise their coins

Initially I invested in Westville, but after observing all the other players investing in Allshire, I followed suit and invested in Allshire. then a player kept his coin, but enough invested in Allshire to meet the quota and 1 more player could keep the coin with Allshire still meeting it's quota. So from then on I generally kept the coin to maximise my winnings. at the beginning of each round i always started by investing in Allshire and if Allshire missed its quota I would have invested back in Allshire the next round.

My strategy was to get the most coins I could for myself, by trying to guess what everyone else would go for. I felt good when I saw that the majority were going for Allshire but confused as to why others would pick any other way.

I just wanted to consistently ensure everyone got the most by investing into Allshire every round. I did not want to try and play any other strategy as it would be too inconsistent. If I just kept consistent and stayed with the single investment, then I could get 150% more than I otherwise would had I just kept the coin.
I was just playing to get as many coins as I could.
great study, thanks
i was hoping that once we met a good balance it would continue that way
the game was fun
it worked best when we thought about everyone, that was how to  maximise points
I decided to mainly go with Allshire to maximize the group's winnings.

I felt that by always voting Allshire, I would generally guarantee 2.5 coins every round as long as others had the same thought process. Selecting other options would put the whole group at risk and wouldn't give me a guaranteed bonus
i thought the game was interesting and made me become a little competitive in wanting to gain the most coins
At first i invested in Allshire and even in Westville but people kept stealing the pot so i mostly kept the coin for myself in the end.
i felt that by giving coin to allshire it was the best strategy for maximising my income - especially as that was obviously what the others were doing!
It was a fun game to play and I tried altering my tactics to see which would get me the best outcome.
It was unrealistic and the 'other players ' were not real. No one would take 1 coin when by click Allshire after the first round they could have had 2-5 each time. People just don't work that way.
i wanted us to win a fair amount as a group

I began by supporting Westville, but then found I wasn't earning any coins as people were choosing to keep the coins for themselves. In order to maximise my own return, I also then began doing this and keeping the coins.
I started by playing for Allshire but then got stung on the next two rounds as people started to keep their coin, so I then just kept my coin as at least I was earning something.
went for allshire despite some more selfish players
Used the graphs to predict the best outcome

I felt the best result for everyone was if we all contributed a coin to Allshire. 2.5 for everyone is a result that everyone should be happy with. Admittedly 3.5 in a round is achievable for up to 2 of the 6 players if they keep their coin, but if everyone goes for that they will get only 1.0 so not worth the risk. Occasionally, when it seemed noone else was keeping the coin, I chose to keep the coin...partly to 'send a message' to others who were considering it (disuading them, because it increases the risk of the 2.0 income for Allshire not being triggered if they don't choose to select it themselves) and partly because those occasions appeared to be a good oppurtunity to increase my own income.     I feel goodwill and gratitude to most of the other members of Allshire for being (mostly) cooperative and pragmatic players.
Started off keeping the coin for myself but then noticed others were investing in Allshire so decided that we'd be better off if we worked together.
my strategy was to meet the allshire target and also maximise my returns

I chose Allshire because it benefited all players and would mean as a group we were able to get the most amount of coins. I was happy when others used the same strategy as me as it was the best outcome. Overall it was an enjoyable task

I went for Allshire and Westville at first, but then noticed others mostly going for keep the coin. I then realised in order to gain more coins, I had to click on keeping the coin as well. It worked most of the time. I felt apprehensive during the game.
I mostly just tried to maximize coins by always voting for the allshire option, but i occasionally kept the coin when it felt like no one else was voting for the allshire option.
I knew the Allshire target was getting met which allowed me to keep the coin for myself
i played safe after the first couple of rounds and held steadfast so my vote was reliable
It was good thanks. And sharing seemed best option.
When i thought others would continue to pick Allshire i clicked on it too so to ensure we had at least 4
Keeping the coin was a guaranteed win even if everyone choosing Allshire would've maximised the total win.
The game was a brain teaser and about how different people react to choices.
I wanted to make sure that my areas were looked after but felt it was my duty as an Allshire resident, to invest in Eastburgh as well as I was able.
I felt we were all thinking the same strategy

My original strategy was to make sure everyone in Allshire would get coins, however after a couple of the Eastburgh players started to vote just for Eastburgh I then moved onto Westville because I would rather everyone gets the same coins then a smaller group getting extra. Once the Eastburgh players started voting Ahhshire again I then decided to keep my Coin to make up for the Coins the Eastburgh players had made me loss.
I wasn't completely sure if I was playing against real players so I did the best to maximise my own winnings.
I wanted to gain as many coins as possible but also help others to gain as many coins as possible
I quite enjoyed the game, now and again I would click on Westville but for the most part I wanted to give everyone a fair chance and went for Allshire target.
Putting money into allshire seemed to be the best collective most for the group. Every once in a while I would pick to keep my coin because it was a bit dull picking the same thing 25 times in a row.
